Conidiogenous cells and developing conidia. 
<emphasis id="1BF74237E62FFFB4E9CBF87CACB4F845" bold="true" box="[136,168,2014,2035]" pageId="8" pageNumber="279">k–l</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="EE83E5A6E62FFFB4E9EDF87CAD08F842" authorityName="Corda" authorityYear="1842" box="[174,276,2014,2036]" class="Incertae sedis" family="Incertae sedis" genus="Mycelium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" order="Incertae sedis" pageId="8" pageNumber="280" phylum="Incertae sedis" rank="genus">Mycelium</taxonomicName>
. 
<emphasis id="1BF74237E62FFFB4E85FF87CAD2CF845" bold="true" box="[284,304,2014,2035]" pageId="8" pageNumber="279">m</emphasis>
