<paragraph id="293C9E25E62EFFB5E9FEFF3FA99EFEFE" blockId="9.[136,1452,157,437]" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">
<emphasis id="1BF74237E62EFFB5E9FEFF3FADD2FF01" bold="true" box="[189,462,157,183]" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">Culture characteristics</emphasis>
: Ascospores germinated on PDA within 20–24 hr at 25−30°C, colonies on PDA reaching 
<quantity id="EE7B33C0E62EFFB5E9CBFF60ACE0FF6A" box="[136,252,194,221]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.75" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" unit="mm" value="3.75" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="2.5">2.5–5 mm</quantity>
diam. after one month, greenish brown, leathery, circular, dense, aerial, reverse dark brown, filamentous. 
<taxonomicName id="EE83E5A6E62EFFB5E9CBFF44ACEAFEB6" authorityName="Corda" authorityYear="1842" box="[136,246,230,256]" class="Incertae sedis" family="Incertae sedis" genus="Mycelium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" order="Incertae sedis" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" phylum="Incertae sedis" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1BF74237E62EFFB5E9CBFF44ACEAFEB6" box="[136,246,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">Mycelium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, brown, pale brown at the apex, septate, constricted at the septa, rough and thick-walled, with a mucilaginous outer wall layer. Colonies on OA reaching 
<quantity id="EE7B33C0E62EFFB5EB32FEA8AEC1FE92" box="[625,733,266,292]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" unit="mm" value="8.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="6.0">6–10 mm</quantity>
diam, producing dense, irregular, flat or effuse, slightly raised, olivaceous grey. Asexual morph sporulated after two months on OA at 25°C, visible as water drop-like on colony.
</paragraph>
